::Rodimus Prime::

Rodimus goes sailing over Cyclonus after the 'monkey flip' was executed. Rodimus flips and lands on his back but he quickly rolls to his feet.

Rodimus fires a few of his arm mounted lasers to stir up the sand in front of Cyclonus. Rodimus tries to use this cover as he again leaps at Cyclonus trying to hand out a forearm shot across the jaw.

Super Cyclonus <supercyclonus@...> wrote:                               
 --- Richard Allen <roborick007@...> wrote:
 
 > ::Rodimus Prime::
 > 
 > Rodimus was ready for a sudden attack and rolled to the side to avoid
 > the blasts. Rodimus then leaps at Cyclonus with all the force his
 > legs would give him. He attempts to 'spear' aka 'football tackle' his
 > enemy.
 
 Cyclonus' face traces a small smile as Rodimus dodges his first attack,
 and only the sand feels the full brunt of Cyclonus' failed attack. Yes
 indeed, Rodimus may still be a worthy opponant. 
 
 With a grunt Cyclonus absorbs the full brunt of Rodimus' attack, and
 turns it! With a spin and twist Cyclonus rolls back, carrying Rodimus
 with him, spinning the Autobot back over him in a sacrifice throw,
 attempting to send Rodimus sailing through the air. As smooth as ever
 Cyclonus continues to roll, sweeping smoothly to his feet. He turns to
 face Rodimus, ready for the Autobot's counter. For the first time a
 small chuckle escapes him, Cyclonus does enjoy a good battle.
 
 Preston
 (Cyclonus)
